OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1782224343
OL,3,CTwo young men admit carrying out cyber
OL,4,Cattack on Transport for London
OL,6,FTwo young men have pleaded guilty to
OL,7,Fcarrying out a cyber attack on
OL,8,FTransport for London (TfL).
OL,10,FThalha Jubair, 20, and Owen Flowers,
OL,11,F18, were arrested in September last
OL,12,Fyear as part of an investigation by
OL,13,Fthe National Crime Agency and City of
OL,14,FLondon Police.
OL,16,FProsecutors said the cyber attack
OL,17,Fresulted in a #39 million loss for TfL
OL,18,Fas well as a "loss of livelihood" for
OL,19,Fpeople dependent on TfL licences,
OL,20,FWestminster Magistrates' Court
OL,21,Fpreviously heard.
OL,26,@zD@NOUzD@aO]
