PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1782224343
OL,3,CTwo young men admit carrying out cyber
OL,4,Cattack on Transport for London
OL,6,FThe NCA previously said investigators
OL,7,Fbelieve the TfL cyber attack was
OL,8,Fcarried out by the criminal hacking
OL,9,Fcollective known as Scattered Spider,
OL,10,Fwhich has been linked to other cyber
OL,11,Fattacks on Jaguar Land Rover and
OL,12,Fretailers including Marks and Spencer.
OL,14,FTfL identified there had been a cyber
OL,15,Fattack on September 1 2024, in which
OL,16,Fcustomer details including names,
OL,17,Fcontact information and Oyster card
OL,18,Frefund data including bank details,
OL,19,Fwere accessed.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/5
